DA MP Phumzile van Damme. JOHANNESBURG - Phumzile Van Damme has resigned as a member of the DA and member of Parliament. She served as a member of parliament for seven years. READ: Maimane resigns from party and parliament Van Damme was also the spokesperson of the party from 2014 to 2018. She says she left the party due to a clique of individuals rather than a "racist party."